WOMEN at Dar es Salaam Water and Sanitation Authority (DAWASA), have commended President Samia Suluhu Hassan for her efforts to accomplish different water projects in the country.By Daily News Reporter They made the remarks recently when they were marching during the women’s day climax at Uhuru Stadium in Dar es Salaam to celebrate the World Women’s Day. Every 8th March women celebrate their day worldwide where they use the day to exchange ideas on their contributions and challenges they are facing in executing their roles at all levels. The theme of this year was equality for sustainable development. Speaking during the climax at Uhuru stadium in Dar es Salaam, Director of Internal Audit at DAWASA, Rosemary Lyamuya, said their organization celebrates women’s day with pride due the tremendous achievement they have made. She said president Samia has been the champion of all their success and majority of Dar es Salaam and Coast regions are now enjoying adequate supply of clean water compared to the situation in the past. "We appreciate the efforts of our president Samia because this cerebration has been a great success, we are happy to see majority of women in this two regions  are no longer supposed to wake up early in the morning and mid night in search for water,” she said She added that there are a lot of water projects going on all around the country, aiming to bring water service close to the people. Some of the areas that are now enjoying full supply of water compared to the past include Kisarawe, Pugu, Chalinze, Mkuranga and Mbwawa. She said all the achievement has been realized by the presence of women in different managerial positions. Going forward, she expressed gratitude for President Samia’s continued trust on women, pledging to keep working hard for the greater interest of the country’s economic growth and improving provision of social services.